			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Could anyone post my message in the PBAE thread plz?<a name="60723"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 7 04 7:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Could anyone post my message for me? For some reason after entering station name and password, typing it out and hitting sumbmit, it sends me back to my message as if I am editing (there is no edit option). I would appreciate it, thx.
<br />

<br />
This is the link of the thread.
<br />

<br />
http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=1800&amp;no_redir=true
<br />

<br />
This is my message.
<br />
------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
Of all the reasons given for the nerf to take place, only one appears to be a valid concern: content hogging.
<br />

<br />
However, when taking into account in which zones that content hogging takes place and the average number of players on those zones, the concern is no longer valid. If the zone was full the bard would not have 50+ mobs to hog in the first place. If 1 group a day can’t  exp there cause a bard is taking all the mobs, then the few bards that AE there have at least equal rights to the 1 group a day that has to move on to, God forbid, another zone?
<br />

<br />
Lack of programmer free time to implement the fix till now. That is totally Unacceptable.
<br />

<br />
Bards are too powerful and they shouldn’t be able to pull and kill 50+ mobs, it is broken and needs to be fixed. That is a lie. 
<br />

<br />
Necros can get same experience if not better than bards soloing at PoFire Tables, and with no risk whatsoever. Same can be said for enchanters charming in Field1 in PoFire or Tipt. Ever seen what a SoVed Charmed Pooka can do in terms of DPS? And did it not occur to SoE that a chanter can solo Tipt for experience with a charmed pet? Thus, what is really the difference here, the amount of the pull? 50+ mobs versus 1 or 2 at a time? 
<br />

<br />
That being said, I am not calling for nerfs, Necros should be Table soloers with their dots, they already pay the penalty with extensive LFG periods due to the lack of undead mobs at high end content, and chanters should have the DPS power of their pets, since when charm breaks, mob comes to them at full DPS power SoVed and all.
<br />

<br />
Bards creating lag on servers. That is totally unacceptable.
<br />

<br />
As bard, I have the same right to play as a Necro or Chanter. Getting lag? Buy more servers with the money we are giving you, it is not like EQ is free and Sony is a Non-Profit Organization.
<br />

<br />
We are working on a right fix to have as little amount of changes as possible. Another lie.
<br />

<br />
Your only intend is to eliminate AE kiting. Why? It certainly can’t be because of the amount of exp per hour, because other classes can get comparable or better experience. You want to eliminate it because of the amount of mobs being pull. 
<br />

<br />
Again, buy more servers. It is a known fact that you are losing your player base and that you are not making as much money as you thought you would. Also, the DX9 implementation uses more resources. Implementation that was done to someday, yet to come, place a new graphic engine to update the graphics so that you can keep EQ around longer and keep milking the cow with yet more expansions. Expansions which will run on the very same servers you have today, thus in your eyes the need to eliminate AE kiting. Thus, please don&#180;t insult our intelligence by sugar coating it and justifying it by saying you are going to be “fair” about it. You might be somewhat new to EQ as you said, but we have been suffering nerfs from day 1.
<br />

<br />
Extended Notes AA were never intended to be used for anything but beneficial songs. Lie.
<br />

<br />
Extended Notes AA nerf was introduced when bards were soloing PoFire. It was a direct response to AA gain differential versus other classes, as well as satisfying the whiny masses. If AE kite is removed from the game, then Extended Notes AA should once again affect all songs, since as you say you find no reason why focus effects don’t work with us bards, and there is no change incoming in the near future that will enable bard to benefit from them. Actually, there is a change, focus effects are halved when using level 66+ spells. Nice slap on the face to all that worked hard getting PoTime and KT flagged to get the nifty focus effects only to render them useless 2 expansions later, just so you can sell new level 70 nifty focus items on next expansions to come.
<br />

<br />
Bard is the only class that can kite 50+ mobs and that is unbalanced and needs to be fix. While it might be true that bards is the only class that can pull 50+ mobs consistently, bard is also the only class that cast on the run, shouldn’t you eliminate cast on the run as well for the shake of the argument?
<br />

<br />

<br />
In all, I am just tired of a company that continuously lies, has no regard whatsoever for its paying customers, and with the only focus in mind of  keeping the customers for as long as possible, regardless of whether the game is becoming more fun to play or not (i.e: Due to the new-expansion-meaner-mob-uberest-yet-loot focus in place since PoP) it now takes at least 1 hour to get a KT group going, since group make up is constrained so much by needing certain classes before you can even thing on grouping there.
<br />

<br />
A company that admittedly says they planned on level 70 players for GoD content, while unofficially cutting the expansion in half postponing the level increases for the customers to pay for it twice, only to later saying “Oops, we screwed up” and doing nothing about it. 
<br />

<br />
Also, nerfing one class down only puts another class on top of the who to nerf next list. Overall, it just limits the game. Things that could be accomplished cannot be done any longer. That coupled with the new mob group requirements in order to get anything done, just takes most of the fun out of the game.
<br />

<br />
Making clerics having to run naked and with no invisible spell all the way from Natimbi to Tipt or Vexed is not fun. 
<br />

<br />
Praying for the 18 sec bard DA to hold so all the group makes it to ikkinz2 in one piece is not fun (if no mage in group).
<br />

<br />
Making the entrance of Ikkinz2 a random hall is not fun.
<br />

<br />
Having to wait 1 hour for your corpse to pop out of an ikkinz zone is not fun.
<br />

<br />
The Trial should be Tipt, Vxed or Ikkinz, NOT getting to the trial IMO.
<br />
 
<br />
I play, among others, a 65 chanter (main), 65 bard and 65 necro. All suffered nerfs regularly, and as contradictive as it might sound, OOW is the only expansion I have pre-ordered, instead of waiting to see if it is going to be worth it or not. On the other hand, LoY is the only expansion I have not bought, IMO is lame, but specially, the maps, the more banking storage and the raid tools should ALL have been introduced via patch. 
<br />

<br />
I do not AE with bard at all, there are more fun ways of getting AA for me than running in circles. This is not about saving bard AE, this is about the game being less and less fun, and SoE reinforcing it with stupid nerfs that only limit gameplay. Nerfs makes people mad and more will leave with each new “balancing for all fairness” nerf. The balancing argument is such a fallacy, if you want a game balanced then make EVERYONE as able to solo as a Warrior, else just say “tough luck, sucks to be you” to whoever is getting nerfed. 
<br />

<br />
Why did I pre-order OOW? Well, WoW is just around the corner, but not there yet.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
