				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Could anyone post my message in the PBAE thread plz?<a name="60894"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 7 04 11:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Since the other thread seems to have been significantly derailed, i'll post here.
<br />

<br />
This is exactly the problem.  They nerf before the problem is fully defined, and i'm sure we are all sick of it to say the least.  Whether or not you agree with AE kiting is not the issue.  I would classify that as a rules of conduct issue, which could easily be solved with creativity ( maybe a summon if so many mobs have you on aggro for certain period of time regardless of level..would still keep swarming alive since the aggro would transfer.)
<br />

<br />
The issue is with sony placating the whining masses by fixing a non-existant problem.  Bards arent the only class to be hit with the nerf bat.  This has been happening for ages, and will continue to happen.  It's the &quot;grass is always greener&quot; syndrome.  For some reason people got the idea that ALL the classes are supposed to be balanced, none being able to outdo the other.  Well so sorry, but this can't and shouldnt be the case.  Warrior are meatshields, wizards are the feeble spell casters etc.  It's the nature of the beast.
<br />

<br />
If they truly didnt want bards to kite, they wouldnt have given us super speed.  While the travel aspect is nice, the first thing a good player is going to do is figure out how to use it in combat.   Someone will watch, catch on, rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
Instead of nerfing they should do something constructive..like i dunno...program some AI.  The mobs in eq are STUPID.  The combat engine they use could be coded by a bored highschool student.  As it stands, its nothing more than a random number generator tied to a clock, whoopity doo.  If they want to stop stop all the kiter then have the mobs pick up rocks and throw them, maybe cast some nukes if being kited. I dont know a single mob that actually uses a bow and arrow. Even the new Kyv models in GoD get face to face to use a bow.  Why cant the mobs try and kite us?
<br />

<br />
The players look for creative ways to use the abilities they have been given, maybe the developers should look at creative ways to fight back.</span></td>
